SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 741
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Tyler Williams of
Gatlinburg-Pittman High School on being named
Region I-3A Coach of the Year.
WHEREAS, we take great pleasure in paying tribute to those outstanding coaches who,
through hard work and commitment, distinguish themselves among the storied coaches and
legendary high school programs of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, Tyler Williams of Gatlinburg-Pittman High School was recently named the
Region 1-3A Coach of the Year, an honor that truly reflects the commitment to athletic
excellence displayed by Coach Williams and the Gatlinburg-Pittman Highlanders; and
WHEREAS, Coach Williams led the Highlanders to their first ever state championship
game after enjoying an undefeated regular season and postseason leading up to the
championship; and
WHEREAS, prior to being named head coach in 2024, Tyler Williams served as
offensive coordinator for the Highlanders and in other positions for seven seasons; and
WHEREAS, Coach Tyler Williams epitomizes the spirit and commitment that are
characteristic of a true Tennessean; he has served with great diligence and dedication,
positively influencing the lives of countless young people with his display of character and
integrity; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud Tyler Williams for his
outstanding leadership as head coach of the Gatlinburg-Pittman High School football team;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Tyler Williams of
